data.value: HOMOZYGOTES HAVE A WT PHENOTYPE. ROOT BENDING AND ROOT ELONGATION ASSAYS UNDER OSMOTIC AND ABA TREATMENTS SHOWED NO SIGNIFICANT DIFFERENCE COMPARED TO WT. HOWEVER,  PRIMARY ROOT ELONGATION WAS INHIBITED BY SALT STRESS. RELATIVE ELECTROLYTE LEAKAGE WAS SIGNIFICANTLY HIGHER IN SALT - STRESSED PLANTS AS COMPARED TO WT
DOUBLE MUTANT ROOTS WERE SIGNIFICANTLY SHORTER THAN WT TOOTS WHEN UNDER SALT-STRESS
SECONDARY CELL WALLS ACCUMULATE IN PITH PARENCHYMA CELLS
